snippet.textDisplay: Vol-au-vent means something along the lines of "bird in the wind" or "flight in the wind" and refers to poached chicken, soup meatballs and mushrooms in a velouté sauce. It's often served in one of those puff pastry cups but those are just puff pastry cups, the vol-au-vent is the filling.
